olive oil
½ unit lemon
1 clove garlic
1 packet garlic aioli
1 bag slaw mix
1 sachet Mexican Fiesta spice blend
1 packet Mild Chipotle Sauce
1 packet pulled pork
6 unit Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 bunch coriander

Slice the lemon (see ingredients list) into wedges. Finely chop the garlic (or use a garlic press). Roughly chop the coriander.

In a small bowl, combine the garlic aioli with a generous squeeze of lemon juice and a pinch of salt and pepper. Set aside.

SPICY! The spice blend is hot, use less if you're sensitive to heat. In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Add the pulled pork, garlic and Mexican Fiesta spice blend and cook until fragrant, 2 minutes.

In a large bowl, add the lemony aioli, slaw mix and coriander and toss to combine.

Heat the mini flour tortillas in a sandwich press or on a plate in the microwave for 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

Bring everything to the table to serve. Build your tacos by filling the tortillas with the slaw, pulled pork and shredded Cheddar cheese. Drizzle over the mild chipotle sauce. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges.